snippet:
Es la primera vez que e venido a este hospital .. literalmente jamás volveré por mas que esté mi vida en juego .. siempre e ido al hospital la princesa.. entre otros y jamás me han demorado tanto como este hospital 5 horas y hasta ahora no me atienden .. me acerco a preguntar si me van atender .. y el jefe de enfermeros es un mal educado .. despota .. me dice .. si usted a venido a las 7:25pm y es el primero pero si viene alguien con mayor prioridad será atendido ENTENDIDO .. muy en cambio su compañera amablemente ya será atendido si .. y el otro como si le pidiera un favor .. me viene mal .. me quede dormido esperando .. y sigo con dolores .. pero jamás volveré .. qué deprimente la atención .. en los demás hospitales son lo mejor.
Agradezco mucho la atención pero no regresaré y siendo las 23:53 aún no soy ni siquiera atendido.
user.name: Carlos Saul Valderrama Ventura

extracted_snippet.translated:
It is the first time that I have come to this hospital.. I will literally never return no matter how much my life is at stake.. I have always gone to the princess hospital.. among others and they have never taken me as long as this hospital, 5 hours and until now They don't attend to me.. I come up to ask if they are going to attend to me.. and the head nurse is rude.. a despot.. he tells me.. yes, you have come at 7:25pm and you are the first but if someone comes with greater priority he will be attended to UNDERSTOOD .. on the other hand his partner will kindly be attended to if .. and the other as if asking him for a favor .. it is bad for me .. I fell asleep waiting .. and I am still in pain .. but never I will return.. how depressing the care.. in the other hospitals they are the best.
I really appreciate the attention but I will not return and at 11:53 p.m. I still haven't even been attended to.

snippet:
Vergonzoso. A mi madre la dijeron ayer en urgencias que a lo mejor la operaban del brazo y que no lo sabian seguro. Que la llamarian. Pero no la han llamado, la han mandado un mensaje del Anestesista. Dan un tfno., en el mensaje para que llamemos, pero directamente lo tienen descolgado. Por cierto a mi madre no la duele su brazo, lo tiene roto pero sin dolor, pero da igual lo importante, es que un nuevo residente aprenda a operar.
Somos personas no cosas, no nos despersonalicen. Somos pacientes, no muñecos que se ponen encima de una mesa de operaciones. Y apreciamos que nos escuchen, pero como ustedes no lo hacen, yo lo escribo aqui para que el resto de pacientes, vean como esta la situación en su hospital.
Y pongo una estrella porque me obliga google para publicar la reseña, que sino les pondría un CERO ¡¡¡
user.name: Lidia Yelmo Rodriguez

extracted_snippet.translated:
Shameful. They told my mother yesterday in the emergency room that they might have surgery on her arm and that they didn't know for sure. That they would call her. But they haven't called her, they have sent her a message from the Anesthetist. They give a phone number in the message for us to call, but they have it picked up directly. By the way, my mother's arm doesn't hurt, it's broken but not in pain, but what's important is that a new resident learns to operate.
We are people, not things, don't depersonalize us. We are patients, not dolls that are placed on an operating table. And we appreciate that you listen to us, but since you don't, I write it here so that the rest of the patients can see what the situation is like in their hospital.
And I put a star because Google forces me to publish the review, otherwise I would give them a ZERO!!!
